                                                                                            <p class="word-copy-lh-mb" style="margin-bottom:12.0pt;"><a href="https://english.uconn.edu/person/serkan-gorkemli/"><strong>Serkan Görkemli</strong></a>&nbsp;is the author of <em>Sweet Tooth and Other Stories</em> (University Press of Kentucky) and <em>Grassroots Literacies: Lesbian and Gay Activism and the Internet in Turkey</em> (SUNY Press), winner of the 2015 Lavender Rhetorics Book Award presented by the Conference on College Composition and Communication. Originally from Türkiye, he is an associate professor of English at the University of Connecticut and lives in New York.</p>
